The paper discusses the application of the partially observable hidden Markov model to keystroke dynamics, which is a biometric authentication system. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model compared to other anomaly detectors, which involves machine learning and statistical analysis, making it relevant to categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metadata and event types, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
